<p>them and send them our photographs also, and tell them that if they are only able to write in English that we will be able to read it as a friend of ours now (reads English?).<br/>Dear friend, I finish my letter in wishing you a big kiss from all the children and from us also.  Do not forget to give the message to all your friends for which I thank you in advance for their remembrances in the shape of their photos.  Au revoir, soon to have news of you I hope.  Simone and Robert embrace you from far away.</p>
<p>I remain your devoiree for life<br/>Madame Ceutevete Jean Baptiste<br/>Rue de l'Asie No. 82<br/>Marcinelle [indecipherable]<br/>Hainaut<br/>Belgique</p>
<p>Give my address to all the friends, do not forget.</p>
